---
import DsSectionHeader from "./DsSectionHeader.astro";

interface Props {
  isIsolated?: boolean;
  isolatedComponentId?: string;
}
const { isIsolated = false } = Astro.props;
---

<DsSectionHeader
  title="Layout System"
  url={isIsolated ? "/resources/design-system" : "/resources/design-system/layout"}
  isIsolated={isIsolated}
/>

<p>The Avionics layout system uses a sophisticated CSS Grid approach for responsive, content-focused layouts.</p>

<h3>Prose Contexts</h3>
<p>We distinguish between generic prose and article content:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>.prose</code>: Generic typography styles for any text block.</li>
  <li><code>.content-prose</code>: Enhanced styles for long-form articles, including specific spacing for headings and lists.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Spacing Tokens</h3>
<pre><code>--s-grid: 24px;       /* Base grid unit */
--s-gap: 1.5rem;      /* Standard gap between elements */
--s-container: 800px; /* Maximum content width (legacy) */</code></pre>

<h3>Grid Layout System</h3>
<p>The grid layout creates three named columns for flexible content placement:</p>

<pre><code>--s-content-max: 67ch; /* Optimal reading width */</code></pre>

<p>This creates three content zones:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>content</strong> (67ch max): Default for body text, optimal reading width</li>
  <li><strong>breakout</strong>: Wider zone for tables, code blocks, images</li>
  <li><strong>full</strong>: Full-width zone for backgrounds, hero sections</li>
</ol>

<h3>Spec Grid</h3>
<p>A responsive grid for card collections (Concepts, Patterns, Practices):</p>
<pre><code>.spec-grid {`{`}
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: var(--s-gap);
{`}`}</code></pre>
